  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Integrated Services and Promotion of Social Cohesion Through a Migrant Coordination and Harmonization Centre in Adana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to continue its support to local authorities in implementing a model for integrated multi-sector service delivery to migrants, refugees and other vulnerable groups in Turkey with the aim of promoting social cohesion with the host community. The first component of this project is to continue ensuring that the established Migrant Coordination and Harmonization Center (the Center) for migrants and refugees provide counselling and referral services, as well as supporting existing municipality services through financial and in-kind support to include migrant and refugee groups in their actions. The second component seeks to strengthen the capacity of relevant stakeholders including the municipality, local public institutions and NGOs to work with and for migrants, refugees and the host community through comprehensive technical assistance and capacity building actions. The third project component enhances consultation and communication channels among migrants, refugees, and host community members in order to enhance dialogue and social cohesion in selected municipalities while aiming to reduce inter-communal tensions that may arise from real and perceived competition for employment, resources and access to public services. Collectively, these components continue to ensure that local authorities have the framework in place to sustainably operate the services tailored for migrants and refugees via the Center as well as other mainstreaming efforts.</narrative>
  </description>
